{
  "texts": [
    "This technique enables simultaneous recordings from multiple locations, allowing researchers to capture the spatiotemporal dynamics of electrical activity across the entire cell population.",
    "However, simultaneous recordings from multiple locations generate a large amount of data, and the interpretation of such complex datasets may pose challenges.",
    "To tackle this, Jurkiewicz et al. (2021) implemented an SVM to analyze signals recorded from hiPSC-CMs on MEAs.",
    "Within MEA readings, intracellular APs can be directly measured via electroporation or indirectly via extracellular field potentials (FPs).",
    "The SVM was used to filter MEA recorded signals into APs and FPs, classify signals as usable or unusable, and extract AP features from the signals."
  ]
}